 1995-05631995-04-040,  IA&ND,  ,  ,  , 
PrecisAppointment of ALEC C. ROBERTSON, of Vancouver, British Columbia, as the Chief British Columbia Treaty Commissioner to hold office during pleasure for a term of three years, effective May 15, 1995; re-appointment of CAROLE T. CORCORAN, of Queen Charlotte, British Collumbia, as a British Columbia Treaty Commissioner to hold office during pleasure for a term of two years, effective April 14, 1995; re-appointment of BARBARA L. FISHER, of Vancouver, British Columbia, as a British Columbia Treaty Commissioner to hold office during pleasure for a term of two years, effective April 14, 1995; and appointment of PETER A. LUSZTIG, of Vancouver, British Columbia, as a British Columbia Treaty Commissioner to hold office during pleasure for a term of two years, effective April 14, 1995.
